  "prompt": "What is distance over time?",
  "response": "Distance over time is a fundamental concept in physics and mathematics that describes the rate at which an object moves from one point to another. It is typically represented by the formula:\n\nSpeed = Distance \u00f7 Time\n\nKey points:\n1. Measures how fast an object is moving\n2. Usually expressed in units like miles per hour (mph) or kilometers per hour (km/h)\n3. Can be calculated by dividing total distance traveled by the total time taken\n4. Important in understanding motion and travel\n\nExample:\nIf a car travels 120 miles in 2 hours, its speed would be:\n120 miles \u00f7 2 hours = 60 miles per hour",
